# Include Directory

This directory contains all header files (.h) for the DC Motor Control project.

## Header Files

### motor.h
Defines the Motor class for controlling a DC motor via L293D motor driver.
- **Pins**: D9 (IN1), D10 (IN2) - PWM capable
- **Features**: Bidirectional control, PWM speed control
- **Range**: -100 (full reverse) to +100 (full forward)
- **Note**: EN pin tied HIGH with 10kΩ resistor (always enabled)

### led.h
Defines the StatusLED class for RGB LED visual feedback.
- **Pins**: D3 (Red), D11 (Green), D2 (Blue - Error indicator)
- **Features**: Smooth color transitions, blinking effects, error mode
- **Color Mapping**: Red (0%) → Yellow (50%) → Green (100%)
- **Error Mode**: Blue LED blinks at 500ms intervals for invalid sensor readings

### display.h
Defines the Display class for OLED status display.
- **Pins**: AD4 (SDA), AD5 (SCL) - I2C interface
- **Display**: SSD1306 128x64 OLED via I2C
- **Features**: Distance readout, PWM percentage with direction (FWD/REV), status bar
- **Library**: U8g2 (olikraus/U8g2@^2.35.30)
- **Optimization**: Uses smaller fonts to reduce RAM usage

### ultraSonic.h
Defines the UltraSonic class for HC-SR04 distance sensor.
- **Pins**: D5 (TRIG), D6 (ECHO)
- **Features**: Distance measurement in centimeters
- **Range**: 2-400 cm
- **Timeout**: Returns 0 when duration >= 38ms (no object detected)
- **Calculation**: distance = duration / 58

## Usage

All header files use `#pragma once` for include guards and are designed to work with Arduino framework. Include them in your source files as needed:

```cpp
#include "motor.h"
#include "ultraSonic.h"
#include "led.h"
```

## Pin Summary

| Component | Pin | Arduino |
|-----------|-----|---------|
| Motor IN1 | D9 | Digital 9 (PWM) |
| Motor IN2 | D10 | Digital 10 (PWM) |
| Ultrasonic TRIG | D5 | Digital 5 |
| Ultrasonic ECHO | D6 | Digital 6 |
| LED Red | D3 | Digital 3 (PWM) |
| LED Green | D11 | Digital 11 (PWM) |
| LED Blue | D2 | Digital 2 (Error) |
| OLED SDA | AD4 | Analog 4 (I2C) |
| OLED SCL | AD5 | Analog 5 (I2C) |

## Notes

- L293D EN pin is tied HIGH with 10kΩ resistor (always enabled)
- All classes follow public/private encapsulation principles
- Static constants are used for pin definitions
- Classes are designed for Arduino Uno R3 compatibility
